# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# /etc/sudoers.d/s7-samuel-skills
#
# Lets the s7 user run the specific Samuel-runnable repair skills
# under sudo without a password prompt, so the persona-chat skill
# runner can invoke them autonomously after a 'yes' confirmation
# without needing a human to type a password.
#
# This is locked to:
#   - The s7 user (no one else)
#   - The exact script paths (no PATH search, no aliases)
#   - The exact set of skills approved for autonomous escalation
#     (only fix-pod.sh and fix-firewall.sh — no general shell access)
#
# Every invocation is audited by sudo's own logging in /var/log/secure.
# Combined with the persona-chat ops ledger and the script-internal
# ops ledgers, that's three independent audit trails for any
# autonomous root action.
#
# DEPLOYMENT (one-time, requires root):
#   sudo install -m 440 -o root -g root \
#     /s7/skyqubi-private/install/sudoers.d/s7-samuel-skills \
#     /etc/sudoers.d/s7-samuel-skills
#   sudo visudo -c    # validate
#
# REMOVAL (one-time, requires root):
#   sudo rm /etc/sudoers.d/s7-samuel-skills
#
# This file is NOT auto-deployed by the installer (yet). It sits in
# the repo as a code asset until Jamie explicitly authorizes deploying
# it. The Pass 2 installer will offer it as an opt-in step.
#
# Governing rules:
#   feedback_three_rules.md      Rule 3: Protect the QUBi
#   project_chat_personas.md     Samuel = FACTS / sysadmin / security
#   engine/agents/samuel_runnable_scripts.yaml  Catalog must match
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# Allow s7 user to run the two repair skills as root, no password.
# Each line is a single command spec. Adding a script here is a
# covenant-level change and must be reviewed.
s7 ALL=(root) NOPASSWD: /s7/skyqubi-private/install/fix-pod.sh
s7 ALL=(root) NOPASSWD: /s7/skyqubi-private/install/fix-firewall.sh

# Defense in depth: explicitly deny shell escapes via the listed scripts.
# (The scripts themselves have no shell-out paths but this catches any
# future change that introduces one.)
Defaults!/s7/skyqubi-private/install/fix-pod.sh      !shell_noargs
Defaults!/s7/skyqubi-private/install/fix-firewall.sh !shell_noargs
